President Obama has signed an emergency declaration for the State of Kansas due to flooding. This declaration allows the Department of Homeland Security and FEMA to coordinate relief efforts and provide assistance to affected areas. FEMA is authorized to provide equipment and resources to alleviate the impacts of the emergency, and emergency protective measures will be funded at 75 percent by the federal government. Bradley Harris has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. For further information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.